net.dv8tion.jda.core.managers.fields

Class Field<T,M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dv8tion.jda.core.managers.fields.Field<T,M>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The Field-Type for this Field. This Type represents the value that will be modified by the manager
    M - The Manager-Type for this Field. This Type represents the Manager that is returned by setValue(Object) for chaining convenience.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AccountField, ApplicationField, ChannelField, EmoteField, GuildField, RoleField, WebhookField

    public abstract class Field<T,M>
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract Manager-Field (AMF)
    This is utilized in updatable Managers. Managers that allow users to modify multiple Fields of an entity.

    Most managers have specific implementations that provide needed functionality and specify behaviour.

    This class is abstract and requires an implementation for checkValue(Object)

    Since:
    3.0

      • setValue

        public M setValue(T value)
        Sets the value which should be used in the update operation for the Manager instance.
        This will cause isSet() to return true!

        Values might be checked differently depending on the Field implementation.
        The check criteria are specified in the field getter of the updatable manager.

        Parameters:
        value - The value that should be used by the update operation
        Returns:
        The specific manager instance for chaining convenience
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the provided value does not pass the specified checks
        See Also:
        isSet()
